description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a Band 6 Radiographer to join our department at the Princess Royal Hospital, in Haywards Heath. This is an exciting opportunity to develop experience of working in a busy CT department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department prides itself on it&#39;s friendly, close-knit, supportive team and is currently undergoing a significant redevelopment project.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Imaging at Princess Royal Hospital consists of 3 DR x-ray rooms, with separate fluoroscopy services. We have recently updated one of our two CT scanners, to a 512 slice, on which we obtain 1-beat cardiac scans. The second 64-slice CT scanner is also being replaced this year. The successful candidate will receive training in CT cardiac and colon procedures, as well as a range of specialist Imaging examinations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Band 6 Radiographer you will rotate through CT, plain film, fluoroscopy, mobile and theatre imaging. There is an out of hours/extended working day commitment to provide a 24 hour emergency imaging service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suitable applicants should be HCPC registered, have post-qualification experience in a similar setting and have a flexible approach to work. As a Band 6 Radiographer, you will be expected to actively partake in the role development of others, working closely with other Radiographers, students and assistant practitioners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Department is supported by a team of Lead Superintendent Radiographers and Superintendent Radiographers. In return for your commitment to us we will provide ongoing support for your professional development, as well as a friendly, challenging and stimulating work environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Jemma Deane&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Lead Superintendent Radiographer, PRH Imaging&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address jemma.deane@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01444 441881 ext 8326&lt;/p&gt;
